originalText.text:
These are supposed to be easy non-issue reviews. On 7-9-2020 I used this garage to park my bicycle. About 3 hours later I came, picked up my bike and was trying to wheel it out of the garage but it wouldn't wheel. The back wheel was bent out of shape and wouldn't spin. The attendant had no idea what happened and seemed clueless as to how the bike could have gotten damaged. I then had to carry the bike 1/2 mile to spokesman for repair costing me $80. If you decide to leave your bike here, please make sure then put it in a secure place and that it won't get hit by a car or something else.

The address is 110  E 57th Street, New York, NY, 10022
